    "Bug-level F8 completion rate 22% -> 78% via shrink starter kit + V-first priority (build 338). User: 'a lot of players hitting the bug level but not completing it. can we help that?' Audit on the 7 F8-stuck failures from build 337: 3 came via warp-forced F6 -> F8 (s=88 elf, 167 dwarf, 500 human) and ALL THREE had final-inventory bug-weapons=[], bug-armors=[], heal-pots=[] -- they punched Dung Beetle Lords for 1 damage with their fists ('Pounding on a Dung Beetle Lord with your fists won't hurt it much!') because regular gear is too big to wield while shrunk and they had no time to find a vendor before dying (33-36T survival on F8). Two coordinated fixes. (1) game_systems._trigger_shrinking_spell now also adds 1 Stinger Blade + 1 Nectar Vial to inventory -- an emergency loadout so the warp-forced agent isn't unarmed. (2) Shrunken tier order swapped: V (vendor) first, then C (chests), then M (monsters), then other beneficials. The bug merchant stocks 2 bug weapons + 2 bug armors + 2-3 Nectar Vials, so reaching V is the highest-leverage move when shrunk. Chest still on the path (Growth Mushroom guaranteed in one). 90-run forced-bug grid: F8-reached held at 9/90 (F1-F7 attrition unchanged), F9-reached 6 -> 7, quest wins 2 -> 6+, F8-stuck 7 -> 2 (167_dwarf still starves after gearing up, 500_human gets one-shot by a Stinkbug Brute special at T1918). The build-337 quest-feasibility milestone is now a quest-RELIABILITY milestone.",
    "Bug-level quest WINNABLE: buffed bug-gear + Growth Mushroom consume gate (build 337). User picked lever 2 from the prior round: buff bug-gear damage so each swing closes the HP race. Bug weapons attack_bonus 4-8 -> 9-16, bug armors defense_bonus 3-6 -> 6-12, levels 1-2 -> 2-3 so the equip filter accepts them at F8 expectations. First grid run surfaced the smoking gun: s=777 human reached F8, opened a chest with the Growth Mushroom (Mablung Crownless, slot 15), and STARVED holding the cure -- the inventory cascade had no gate matching potion_type='growth_mushroom'. Mushroom was in inv for 2000+ turns unused. Two fixes wired. (1) inventory mode: TOP priority Growth Mushroom consume when shrunk + holding the mushroom. (2) game_loop: open inventory when shrunk + has_mushroom, gated on last_action not in (i,x). Also added is_shrunk early-return to is_truly_trapped() so the no-D/no-U/no-W early-terminate doesn't fire on the sealed bug-level floor (chest-borne Mushroom + Bug Queen kill are escapes the gate can't see). 90-run forced-bug-level grid: 9/90 reached F8 (F1-F7 attrition still the bottleneck), 2/9 of those completed the quest -- s=777 human ate mushroom T~2841 then descended F8->F9 stairs and died F9 to a Vault Guardian Golem; s=47 dwarf actually completed the quest TWICE (un-shrunk, ascended F8->F7, redescended re-shrunk, un-shrunk again, descended F8->F9, reached F11). Quest-completion rate among F8-reachers: 0/24 -> 2/9 (22%).",
    "Bug-level quest probe: chest-first shrunken priority + no-flee on sealed floors (build 336). User: 'can the playtester complete the bug level quest?' Across the prior 5000-turn grid, 24 runs reached F8+ (playtest mode force-spawns the Bug Level there) and 0 cleared the quest -- 5 confirmed shrunken via the 'Zot's shrinking spell prevents you from leaving!' log, none found a Growth Mushroom or defeated the Bug Queen. Trace on s=317 human F8: agent opened 2 of 7 chests in a 3x3 reachable pocket (neither had has_growth_mushroom), then bounced flee->re-engage->flee for 1500T against Ant Soldiers and Snails at HP 17-25/82. Root causes: (1) policy gave chests no priority lift while shrunk so the bounded-risk path to the guaranteed Growth Mushroom competed with normal beneficials; (2) low-HP-flee (hp_pct<0.30, no heal options) and monster_too_tough flee both fired during shrunken fights even though stairs/warps are sealed -- fleeing just postpones the same fight against the same monster, draining the food clock for nothing. Fix (1): shrunk tiers replaced with [C, V, M, other beneficials, T/N] -- chest hunt first, vendor (bug-gear) second, then commit to combat. Fix (2): both flee gates skipped when is_shrunk. s=317 human flipped 5000T-stuck -> 2156T F8 killed by Firefly Mage (combat death at depth, real cause). Quest still unbeatable: 5 bug-level seeds re-run all died at F8, none reached Bug Queen spawn or found the right chest -- next lever is game-balance (bug monsters out-damage shrunken bug-gear) or seeding a Growth Mushroom into the bug merchant's stock.",
    "Loop hunt round 7: floor-scoped Hail-Mary tracker + early-terminate truly-trapped runs (build 335). User: 'Keep going, I don't want any loops. Make this thing smart!' Caught s=16180 human, 5000T stuck on F3 with 22 unique tiles visited and 0 kills out of 16 monsters. T1665 trace: agent at (3,4), warp_path 2 steps south, D=None, U=north, reach_pct=100. But every 5-7 turns the agent opened inventory, tried 'u6' (unidentified Healing Potion at full HP -- 'Already at full health!', not consumed), then bounced one tile, opened inv, tried 'u6' AGAIN. Root cause: wedge_attempted_actions resets on every move (tile-scoped wedge episode), so a 5-tile bounce loop kept re-trying the same dud item that never consumed. Fix (1): new floor-scoped tracker wedge_tried_this_floor that unions into wedge_attempted, so an item tried once stays tried until the floor changes. Wayfinder reclaims control after the first dud, walks to W, escapes. (2) PlaytestSession.is_truly_trapped + early_terminated flag: if turns_on_floor >= 1500 AND ts_new >= 800 AND reach_pct >= 90 AND no D/U reachable AND no warp AND no Teleport/Descent scroll in inventory, break the main loop instead of burning the rest of the turn budget. Saves 3000+ turns of harness CPU per genuinely-unsalvageable run. Status shows 'stuck: no escape (F2, 1500T on floor, reach 100%)'. s=16180 human flipped from 5000T F3 stuck (0 progress) -> 3658T F8 killed by Fly Swarm -- combat death at depth.",
    "Loop hunt round 6: wedge floors get expiry + permanent escalation (build 334). User: 'Keep going, I don't want any loops. Make this thing smart!' Caught s=88 human 2032T F2 starvation. Trace: agent stair-wedge-escaped F2 at T280 (osc_streak=50, 'u' valve fired, F2 added to wedge_floors). On F1, exhausted reachable region but D pointed back to F2. wedge-floor block stripped D from priority so agent burned 800T searching for warp, eventually wayfinder re-tried D, found F2 still wedged, escape valve fired again -- F1<->F2 cycle for 1500+ turns until food ran out. Three layered fixes. (1) wedge_floors changed from set to dict (z -> turn-added) with 500T expiry; an old wedge marker drops off so the agent can re-try a floor after a long gap (more XP, different fog reveals). (2) wedge_count tracks add-events; after 3 marks a floor becomes PERMANENT (no expiry) -- it has provably resisted multiple escape attempts. permanent_wedge_floors exposed in obs. (3) When D leads to a PERMANENT wedge, both game_loop and warp_mode treat D as unreachable: trapped_no_d's no-D fast-path fires (warp reachable + turns_on_floor >= 150), agent accepts the warp instead of cycling. Mirror gate: if turns_on_floor >= 600 on a 'safe' floor, drop the wedge-floor descent block (safe floor became unsafe, re-try the wedge). s=88 human flipped from 2032T F2 starvation -> 1717T F2 killed by Giant Spider (combat death, faster, real cause). 5000-turn grid: avg max floor 5.14 -> 5.15 (held), alive 6 -> 5 (s=88 now dies to combat), loop_turns_total 12611 -> 12595. Loop floor moved from 'starve in own cycle' to 'die fighting at depth' once more.",
    "Retreat-after-warp gate: +1 floor tolerance (build 332). User: 'Let's keep loop hunting.' Audit on the prior grid: 32 suspicious runs (turn >= 800 + floor <= 3) survived the trapped_no_d easing. Trace on s=99 elf (3893T on F3, 193 kills, 92.6% waste, no loop_turns flagged): T1192 warped F1 -> F2, fully explored F2 to 86% reach with D reachable by T1500, then the wayfinder routed onto a W tile at T1559 and force-warped back to F1. Root cause: retreat_to_floor flag fires when pc.z > max_z_via_stairs, and that threshold was strict-greater so a warp F1 -> F2 instantly triggered retreat mode. Retreat tiers strip D from priority ([U, V] only), so the agent never descends despite D being right there -- it instead routes toward W to ascend back. Eased: retreat now only fires when pc.z > max_z_via_stairs + 1 (a 2+ floor gap). Single-floor warps let the agent stay and descend D normally. 5000-turn grid: avg max floor 4.63 -> 4.83 (+4%), F3 deaths 25 -> 17 (-32%), F4-F7 each +2-3 runs, F11 (1) and F14 (1) reached for the first time, alive held at 2. s=99 elf went 3893T F3 -> 1444T F7 dying to a Wraith -- combat death at depth instead of wandering until starvation.",
    "trapped_no_d gate eased: catches stuck-but-not-quite-90% explorers (build 331). User screenshot of Eomer II (s=99 human, 1261T on F1, 52 kills, starved) prompted the 'high turn + low floor is suspicious' insight. Grid audit: 26 runs matched (turn >= 800 + max floor <= 2), most had loop_turns = 0 because they weren't 2-tile oscillations -- they were diffuse wandering across a small reachable region. s=88 dwarf F2: 28/32 reachable tiles visited (reach_pct = 85%), no new tile in 2000+ turns, BUT trapped_no_d required reach_pct >= 90 so the warp escape valve never fired -- agent burned 2500+ turns wandering until starvation. Eased the gate to two firing paths: (1) reach_pct >= 80% AND no new tile in 200T (was 90% / 200T), (2) no new tile in 500T regardless of reach_pct (covers rare case where reach_pct stays low because fog reveals add BFS-reachable tiles faster than the agent walks them). Mirrored the same in warp_mode. 5000-turn grid: avg max floor 4.15 -> 4.63 (+12%), F1 deaths 23 -> 16, F8+ runs 12 -> 22 (+83%), F9 reached 6 -> 11 (+83%), suspicious-runs 26 -> 14 (-46%), loop_turns_total 16775 -> 12230 (-27%). Agents now warp out of region-split wedges instead of wandering forever, hitting deeper hazards as intended.",
